==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nuts
<hw>nuts</hw> <pr>(n⟦ucr⟧ts)</pr>, <pos>pred. a.</pos> <def>Crazy;
loony; insane; batty; -- used in a predicate position, usually in
phrases such as <ex>to go nuts</ex>, <ex>went nuts</ex>, are you
<ex>nuts</ex>?</def> <mark>[slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nuts</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: nuts
<hw>nuts</hw> <pr>(n⟦ucr⟧ts)</pr>, <pos>interj.</pos> <def>An expression
of disapproval, defiance, or displeasure, as in: ⟦ldquo⟧Ah, nuts! My
knife just broke.⟦rdquo⟧</def> <mark>[slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nut sedge</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>nutsedge</ent>⟦br⟧
